text: The De Havilland Mosquito is a British aircraft from the World War II. The Mosquito was a successful design. Originally intended to be a bomber, the type was very fast, could fly a long way and carry heavy loads. Therefore, it was and it was adapted to a number of other roles such as fighter, night fighter, night intruder, attack, reconnaissance and pathfinder. ==References== Category:British Army equipment Category:Royal Air Force Category:World War II British aircraft
title: De Havilland Mosquito
